This is a web-app so don't pay attention to catering to ios and android versions of Expo. So comptability to ios and android needed.

This is how my database looks : 
1. Items Table

id: int8 (Primary Key, Auto-incrementing)
name: text
description: text
purchase_price: numeric
selling_price: numeric
status: text
qr_code: text
container_id: int8 (Foreign Key, linked to containers.id)
category_id: int8 (Foreign Key, linked to categories.id)
created_at: timestamptz
updated_at: timestamptz
sold_at: timestamptz
created_by: uuid (Foreign Key, linked to auth.users.id)
deleted: bool
user_id: uuid (Foreign Key, linked to auth.users.id)
photo_storage_url: text
2. categories Table

id: int8 (Primary Key, Auto-incrementing)
name: text
description: text
created_at: timestamptz
updated_at: timestamptz
deleted: bool
user_id: uuid (Foreign Key, linked to auth.users.id)
icon: text
3. containers Table

id: int8 (Primary Key, Auto-incrementing)
number: int4
name: text
description: text
qr_code: text
created_at: timestamptz
updated_at: timestamptz
deleted: bool
user_id: uuid (Foreign Key, linked to auth.users.id)
Relationships/Foreign Keys:

Items.container_id references containers.id
Items.category_id references categories.id
Items.created_by references auth.users.id
Items.user_id references auth.users.id
categories.user_id references auth.users.id
containers.user_id references auth.users.id